│ <\n```\n\n**Proposed Change**:\nReplace the block with a simple, correct                   │
│ implementation.\n\n```cpp\ncase scConstant:\n  // A constant is a constant, regardless of  │
│ the new scope.\n  return this;\n```\n\nThis ensures that the function correctly identifies │
│ that a constant's value does not change when moving to an outer scope, preventing the      │
│ incorrect widening operation.\n\n### 5. Conclusion\n\nBy correcting the logic for          │
│ `SCEVConstant` in `SCEV::getSCEVAtScope`, we ensure that the exit value of expressions is  │
│ computed correctly. This resolves the miscompilation by providing the `indvars` pass with  │
│ the correct exit value (`65512`), leading to the generation of correct code."})            │
